“Here is the world. Beautiful and terrible things will happen. Don't be afraid.” Last night, we went searching for Shadow, our friends, @pigpen_the_yota_ and @findmetrekking’s husky, who had disappeared on the backside of Lookout Mountain earlier that day. It was 20°F and we were planning on sleeping on the icy trail where he was last seen. Instead, we bushwhacked down a ravine into a canyon as we followed Loki who was following dog and deer tracks. About 3am, we were stopped by the half frozen Clear Creek, and had to wade across.
We were soaking wet, and it was well below freezing. It wasn’t safe for us to sleep outside any longer. 
We passed out in the camper at the trailhead parking lot about 5am, and woke up to a small army of y’all on Instagram ready to help.

A passing hiker, @ketomountaingirl, spotted Shadow as she made her way down the icy trail with her own two pups.
He had been found in the same spot where Loki was aggressively sniffing and slightly whining the night before.(I guess we have a little ways to go until Loki is a good tracker and I’m a good handler)
Shadow was scared and so cold he couldn’t move for quite a while, but we carried him most of the way out, and all eventually made it back home safe. 
Thank you to you all who showed the love and helped us out in so many ways. We even found coffee, water, and a bag of hand warmers and dog treats on the truck bumper that had been left by one of y’all.
It was a wild night with no guarantee of a happy ending, but it ended up working out.
_

node.text:
Growing up, my parents owned a campground, and in the off season, we saw the rest of America from Baja to Alaska from our own RV.
So the concept of having a home on the open road away from a house ran deep in my family, just like it does with my fur fam now.
Still living on the road as much as we can, you can imagine the gratitude I have for the folks at @gorving, who have been highlighting this passion of my family’s and now supporting our journey after all these years.
_
Hope you love this short video we put our heart and soul into.
